obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (23508)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23508&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the ^1[National Institutes of`
  line `Technology, Science Education and Research] Act, 2007.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^2 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint, and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "National Institutes of Technology" (w.e.f. 7-6-2012).`
  line `2. 15th August, 2007, vide notification No. S.O. 1384(E), dated 9th August, 2007, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part`
  line `II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (23509)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Declaration of certain Institutions as Institutions of national importance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2014, s. 2, for "the First Schedule and the Second Schedule" (w.e.f. 4-3-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23509&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `Whereas the`
  line `objects of the institution mentioned in ^1[the First Schedule, the Second Schedule and the Third Schedule]`
  line `are such as to make them Institutions of national importance, it is hereby declared that each such institute`
  line `is an Institution of national importance.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (23510)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23510&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `.In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,-`
  line
  line `(a) "Board", in relation to any Institute, means the Board of Governors thereof;`
  line
  line `(b) "Chairperson", means the Chairperson of the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) "Corresponding Institute", in relation to a society mentioned in column (2) of ^1[the First`
  line `Schedule, the Second Schedule and the Third Schedule] means the Institute as specified in column (3)`
  line `of ^1[the First Schedule, the Second Schedule and the Third Schedule];`
  line
  line `(d) "Council", means the Council established under sub-section (1) of section 30 ^2[ ^3*** ^4*** as the case may be];`
  line
  line `(e) "Deputy Director", in relation to any Institute, means the Deputy Director thereof;`
  line
  line `(f) "Director", in relation to any Institute, means the Director thereof;`
  line
  line `(g) "Institute" means any of the Institutions mentioned in column (3) of ^1[the First Schedule, the`
  line `Second Schedule and the Third Schedule];`
  line
  line `(h) "Notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(i) "Prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(j) "Registrar" in relation to any Institute, means the Registrar thereof;`
  line
  line `(k) "Schedule" means ^5[the First Schedule, the Second Schedule and the Third Schedule];`
  line
  line `(l) "Senate" in relation to any Institute, means the Senate thereof;`
  line
  line `(m) "Society" means any of the societies registered under the Societies Registration Act, 1860`
  line `(21 of 1860) and mentioned in column (2) of the ^5[the First Schedule, the Second Schedule and the`
  line `Third Schedule];`
  line
  line `(n) "Statutes and Ordinances", in relation to any Institute, means the Statutes and Ordinances of`
  line `that Institute made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2014, s. 2, for "the First Schedule and the Second Schedule" (w.e.f. 4-3-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 28 of 2012, s. 5 (w.e.f. 7-6-2012).`
  line
  line `3. The words, brackets, figures and letter "or sub-section (1) of section 30A" omitted by Act 9 of 2014, s. 3`
  line `(w.e.f. 4-3-2014).`
  line
  line `4. The words "as the case may be" omitted by Act 2 of 2018, s. 3 and The Second Schedule (w.e.f. 5-1-2018).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 9 of 2014, s.3, for "the First Schedule and the Second Schedule" (w.e.f. 4-3-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (23511)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Incorporation of Institutes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23511&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Each of the Institutes mentioned in column (3) of the ^1[the First`
  line `Schedule, the Second Schedule and the Third Schedule] shall be a body corporate having perpetual`
  line `succession and a common seal and shall, by its name, sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `^2[(1A) The Bengal Engineering and Science University, Shibpur shall be deemed to have been`
  line `incorporated under this Act, and on such incorporation, be called the Indian Institute of Engineering`
  line `Science and Technology, Shibpur.]`
  line
  line `(2) The body corporate constituting each of the said Institutes shall consist of a Chairperson, a`
  line `Director and other members of the Board for the time being of the institute.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s.4, ibid., for "the First Schedule and the Second Schedule" (w.e.f. 4-3-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 4-3-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (23512)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Effect of incorporation of Institutes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23512&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `On and from the commencement of this Act,`
  line
  line `(a) Any reference to a society in any law, other than this Act, or in any contract or other`
  line `instrument shall be deemed as a reference to the corresponding Institute;`
  line
  line `(b) All property, movable and immovable, of or belonging to a society shall vest in the`
  line `corresponding Institute;`
  line
  line `(c) All the rights and liabilities of a society shall be transferred to, and be the rights and liabilities`
  line `of the corresponding Institute; and`
  line
  line `(d) every person employed by a society, immediately before such commencement shall hold his`
  line `office or service in the corresponding Institute for the same tenure, at the same remuneration and`
  line `upon the same terms and conditions and with the same rights and privileges as to pension, leave,`
  line `gratuity, provident fund and other matters as he would have held if this Act had not been passed, and`
  line `shall continue to do so unless and until his employment is terminated or until such tenure,`
  line `remuneration and terms and conditions are duly altered by the Statutes:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the alteration so made is not acceptable to such employee, his employment may`
  line `be terminated by the Institute in accordance with the terms of contract with the employee or, if no`
  line `provision is made therein in this behalf, on payment to him by the Institute, of compensation`
  line `equivalent to three months remuneration in the case of permanent employee and one months'`
  line `remuneration in the case of other employee.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5_a:
  sectionId (23513)
  sectionNo 5A
  orderNo 6
  title `Effect of incorporation of Bengal Engineering and Science University, Shibpur.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 4-3-2014)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23513&sectionno=5A&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[5A. Effect of incorporation of Bengal Engineering and Science University, Shibpur.--On and`
  line `from the commencement of the National Institutes of Technology, Science Education and Research`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 2014 (9 of 2014)--`
  line
  line `(a) any reference to the Bengal Engineering and Science University, Shibpur in any law, contract`
  line `or other instrument shall be deemed as a reference to the Indian Institute of Engineering Science and`
  line `Technology, Shibpur;`
  line
  line `(b) all property, movable and immovable, of or belonging to the Bengal Engineering and Science`
  line `University, Shibpur, shall vest in the Indian Institute of Engineering Science and Technology,`
  line Shibpur;
  line
  line `(c) all the rights and liabilities of the Bengal Engineering and Science University, Shibpur shall`
  line `be the rights and liabilities of the Indian Institute of Engineering Science and Technology, Shibpur;`
  line
  line `(d) every person (including Director, officers and other employees) who is employed in the`
  line `Bengal Engineering and Science University, Shibpur, immediately before the date of commencement`
  line `of the National Institutes of Technology, Science Education and Research (Amendment) Act, 2014`
  line `(9 of 2014), shall, on and after such commencement, become an employee of the Indian Institute of`
  line `Engineering Science and Technology, Shibpur and shall hold his office or service by the same tenure,`
  line `at the same remuneration and upon the same terms and conditions and with the same rights and`
  line `privileges as to pension, leave, gratuity, provident fund and other matters as he would have held the`
  line `same on the date of the commencement of the National Institutes of Technology, Science Education`
  line `and Research (Amendment) Act, 2014, as if the said Act had not been brought into force and shall`
  line `continue to do so until his employment is terminated or until such tenure, remuneration, terms and`
  line `conditions are altered by the Statutes or Ordinances:`
  line
  line `Provided that the tenure, remuneration, terms and conditions of service of such person shall not`
  line `be altered to his disadvantage without the previous approval of the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any reference to the Chancellor and the Vice-Chancellor of the Bengal`
  line `Engineering and Science University, Shibpur in any law, instrument or other document made before`
  line `the commencement of the said Act, shall be construed as a reference to the Visitor and the Director,`
  line `respectively, of the Indian Institute of Engineering Science and Technology, Shibpur;`
  line
  line `(e) Vice-Chancellor of the Bengal Engineering and Science University, Shibpur shall be the`
  line `Director of the Indian Institute of Engineering Science and Technology, Shibpur till such date the`
  line `Central Government appoints new Director for the Indian Institute of Engineering Science and`
  line `Technology, Shibpur;`
  line
  line `(f) any examination conducted by the Bengal Engineering and Science University, Shibpur`
  line `immediately before the commencement of the National Institutes of Technology, Science Education`
  line `and Research (Amendment) Act, 2014 (9 of 2014) for admission or award of degrees shall be valid`
  line `examination and shall be deemed to have been conducted by the Indian Institute of Engineering`
  line `Science and Technology, Shibpur.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (23514)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Powers of Institutes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. The words "and the Deputy Director" omitted by Act 28 of 2012, s. 7 (w.e f. 7-6-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23514&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, every Institute shall exercise the`
  line `following powers and perform the following duties, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) to provide for instruction and research in such branches of engineering and technology,`
  line `management, education, sciences and arts, as the Institute may think fit, and for the advancement of`
  line `learning and dissemination of knowledge in such branches;`
  line
  line `(b) to hold examinations and grant degrees, diplomas and other academic distinctions or titles;`
  line
  line `(c) to confer honorary degrees or other distinctions;`
  line
  line `(d) to fix, demand and receive fees and other charges;`
  line
  line `(e) to establish, maintain and manage halls and hostels for the residence of students;`
  line
  line `(f) to supervise and control the residence and regulate the discipline of students of the Institute`
  line `and to make arrangements for promoting their health, general welfare and cultural and corporate life;`
  line
  line `(g) to provide for the maintenance of units of the National Cadet Corps for the students of the`
  line Institute;
  line
  line `(h) to institute academic and other posts with the prior approval of the Central Government, and`
  line `to make appointments thereto excluding the Director ^1***;`
  line
  line `(i) to frame Statutes and Ordinances and to alter, modify or rescind the same;`
  line
  line `(j) to deal with any property belonging to or vested in the institute in such manner as the Institute`
  line `may deem fit for advancing the objects of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(k) to receive gifts, grants, donations or benefactions from the Government and to receive`
  line `bequests, donations and transfers of movable or immovable properties from testators, donors or`
  line `transferors, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(l) to co-operate with educational or other institutions in any part of the world having objects`
  line `wholly or partly similar to those of the Institute by exchange of teachers and scholars and generally in`
  line `such manner as may be conducive to their common objects;`
  line
  line `(m) to institute and award fellowships, scholarships, exhibitions, prizes and medals;`
  line
  line `(n) to undertake consultancy in the areas or disciplines relating to the Institute; and`
  line
  line `(o) to do all such things as may be necessary, incidental or conducive to the attainment of all or`
  line `any of the objects of the Institute.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), an Institute shall not dispose of in any`
  line `manner any immovable property without the prior approval of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (23515)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Institutes to be open to all races, creeds and classes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23515&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Institute shall be open to`
  line `persons of either sex and of whatever race, creed, caste or class, and no test or condition shall be imposed`
  line `as to religious belief or profession in admitting or appointing members, students, teachers or workers or in`
  line `any other connection whatsoever.`
  line
  line `(2) No bequest, donation or transfer of any property shall be accepted by any Institute, which in the`
  line `opinion of the Council involves conditions or obligations opposed to the spirit and object of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (23516)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Teaching at Institutes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23516&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `All teaching at each of the Institutes shall be conducted by or in the name`
  line `of the Institute in accordance with the Statutes and Ordinances made in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (23517)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title Visitor.
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23517&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The President of India shall be the Visitor of every Institute.`
  line
  line `(2) The Visitor may appoint one or more persons to review the work and progress of any Institute and`
  line `to hold inquiries into the affairs thereof and to report thereon in such manner as the Visitor may direct.`
  line
  line `(3) Upon receipt of any such report, the Visitor may take such action and issue such directions as he`
  line `considers necessary in respect of any of the matters dealt with in the report and the Institute shall be`
  line `bound to comply with such directions within reasonable time.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (23518)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Authorities of Institutes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23518&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The following shall be the authorities of an Institute, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a Board of Governors;`
  line
  line `(b) a Senate; and`
  line
  line `(c) such other authorities as may be declared by the Statutes to be the authorities of the`
  line Institute.
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (23519)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Board of Governors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23519&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The Board of every ^1[Institute mentioned in the First Schedule] shall`
  line `consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Chairperson to be nominated by the Visitor;`
  line
  line `(b) the Director, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) two persons not below the rank of the Joint Secretary to the Government of India to be`
  line `nominated by the Central Government from amongst persons dealing with technical education and`
  line finance;
  line
  line `(d) two persons to be nominated by the Government of the State in which the ^2[Institute mentioned in the First Schedule] is situated, from amongst persons, who, in the opinion of that`
  line `Government, are technologists or industrialists of repute;`
  line
  line `(e) two persons, at least one of whom shall be a woman, having special knowledge or practical`
  line `experience in respect of education, engineering or science to be nominated by the Council; ^3***`
  line
  line `(f) one professor and one assistant professor or a lecturer of the ^2[Institute mentioned in the First`
  line `Schedule] to be nominated by the Senate;`
  line
  line `^4[(g) the Director of the Indian Institute of Technology in whose zone the Institute is located, or`
  line `his nominee, not below the rank of a Professor].`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s.8, ibid., for "Institute" (w.e.f. 7-6-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs by Act 28 of 2012, s.8, for "Institute" (w.e.f. 7-6-2012).`
  line
  line `3. The word "and" omitted by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 7-6-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s.8, ibid. (w.e.f. 7-6-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_11_a:
  sectionId (23520)
  sectionNo 11A
  orderNo 13
  title `Board of Institutes of Second Schedule and Third Schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23520&sectionno=11A&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[11A. Boards of Institute of 2[Second Schedule and Third Schedule].-- The Board of every Institute mentioned in ^3[the Second Schedule and the Third Schedule] shall consist of the following`
  line `members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Chairperson to be nominated by the Visitor;`
  line
  line `(b) Secretary, Department of Higher Education, Government of India, or his nominee not below`
  line `the rank of the Joint Secretary to the Government of India, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) Director of the Institute, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) Director of Indian Institute of Science, Bangalore, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) Director of one of the Indian Institutes of Technology, to be nominated by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(f) two Secretaries to the Government of India, to be nominated by the Central Government`
  line `representing its Scientific or Industrial Ministries;`
  line
  line `(g) Chief Secretary of the State in which the Institute is located, or his nominee not below the`
  line `rank of the Joint Secretary to the Government of India, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(h) two professors of the Institute to be nominated by the Senate;`
  line
  line `(i) two eminent scientists, to be nominated by the Council, having special knowledge of practical`
  line `experience in respect of education, engineering or science, one of whom shall be a woman; and`
  line
  line `(j) Financial Advisor, Ministry of Human Resource Development, ex officio.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s.9, ibid. (w.e.f. 7-6-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 9 of 2014, s.6, for "Second Schedule" (w.e.f. 4-3-2014).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s.6, ibid., for "the Second Schedule" (w.e.f. 4-3-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (23521)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 14
  title `Term of office of, vacancies among, and allowances payable to, members of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2012, s. 10 (w.e.f. 7-6-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23521&sectionno=12&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Save as`
  line `otherwise provided in this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) the term of office of the Chairperson or other members of the Board shall be three years from`
  line `the date of his nomination;`
  line
  line `(b) the term of office of an ex officio member shall continue so long as he holds the office by`
  line `virtue of which he is a member;`
  line
  line `(c) the term of office of a member nominated under clause (f) of section 11 ^1[and clause (h) of`
  line `section 11A] shall be two years from the date of his nomination;`
  line
  line `(d) a casual vacancy shall be filled up in accordance with the provisions of section 11 ^1[or section`
  line `11A, as the case may be;]`
  line
  line `(e) the term of office of a member nominated to fill a casual vacancy shall continue for the`
  line `remainder of the term of the member in whose place, he has been nominated;`
  line
  line `(f) the member of the Board shall be entitled to such allowances, if any, from the Institute as may`
  line `be provided for in the Statutes but no member other than the members referred to in clauses (b) and`
  line `(f) of section 11 ^1[and clauses (c) and (h) of section 11A] shall be entitled to any salary by reason of`
  line `this clause.`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (23522)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 15
  title `Powers and functions of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23522&sectionno=13&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Board of every`
  line `Institute shall be responsible for the general superintendence, direction and control of the affairs of the`
  line `Institute and shall exercise all the powers of the Institute not otherwise provided for by this Act, the`
  line `Statutes and the Ordinances, and shall have the power to review the acts of the Senate.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Board of every Institute shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) take decisions on questions of policy relating to the administration and working of the`
  line Institute;
  line
  line `(b) institute courses of study at the Institute;`
  line
  line `(c) make Statutes;`
  line
  line `(d) institute and appoint persons to academic as well as other posts in the Institute;`
  line
  line `(e) consider and modify or cancel Ordinances;`
  line
  line `(f) consider and pass resolutions on the annual report, the annual accounts and the budget`
  line `estimates of the Institute for the next financial year as it thinks fit and submit them to the Council`
  line `together with a statement of its development plans;`
  line
  line `(g) exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as may be conferred or imposed`
  line `upon it by this Act or the Statutes;`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall have the power to appoint such committees, as it considers necessary for the`
  line `exercise of its powers and the performance of its duties under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (23523)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 16
  title Senate.
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23523&sectionno=14&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The Senate of every Institute shall consist of the following persons, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Director, ex officio, who shall be the Chairman of the Senate;`
  line
  line `(b) the Deputy Director, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) the Professors appointed or recognised as such by the Institute for the purpose of imparting`
  line `instructions in the Institute;`
  line
  line `(d) three persons, one of whom shall be a woman, not being employees of the Institute, to be`
  line `nominated by the Chairperson in consultation with the Director, from amongst educationists of`
  line `repute, one each from the field of science, engineering and humanities;`
  line
  line `(e) such other members of the staff as may be laid down in the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (23524)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 17
  title `Functions of Senate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23524&sectionno=15&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Statutes and the Ordinances, the`
  line `Senate of an Institute shall have the control and general regulation, and be responsible for the maintenance of standards of instruction, education and examination in the Institute and shall exercise such`
  line `other powers and perform such other duties as may be conferred or imposed upon it by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (23525)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 18
  title `Chairperson of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23525&sectionno=16&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson shall ordinarily preside at the meetings of the`
  line `Board and at the Convocations of the Institute.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of the Chairperson to ensure that the decisions taken by the Board are`
  line implemented.
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson shall exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as may be`
  line `assigned to him by this Act or the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (23526)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 19
  title `Director and Deputy Director.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23526&sectionno=17&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Director ^1*** of an Institute shall be appointed by the`
  line `Visitor, on such terms and conditions of service and on the recommendations of a Selection Committee`
  line `constituted by him in such manner, as may be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(2) The Director shall be the principal academic and executive officer of the Institute and shall be`
  line `responsible for the proper administration of the Institute and for the imparting of instruction and`
  line `maintenance of discipline therein.`
  line
  line `(3) The Director shall submit annual reports and accounts to the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) The Director shall exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as may be assigned to`
  line `him by this Act or the Statutes or Ordinances.`
  line
  line `^2[(5) The Deputy Director of every Institute shall be appointed in such manner and on such terms and`
  line `conditions as may be laid down by the Statutes and shall exercise such powers and perform such duties as`
  line `may be assigned to him by this Act or the Statutes or by the Director.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "and Deputy Director" omitted by Act 28 of 2012, s.11 (w. e. f 7-6-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for sub-section (5) (w.e.f 7-6-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (23527)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 20
  title Registrar.
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23527&sectionno=18&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Registrar of every Institute shall be appointed on such terms and conditions`
  line `as may be laid down by the Statutes and shall be the custodian of records, the common seal, the funds of`
  line `the Institute and such other property of the Institute as the Board shall commit to his charge.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar shall act as the Secretary of the Board, Senate and such committees as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(3) The Registrar shall be responsible to the Director for the proper discharge of his functions.`
  line
  line `(4) The Registrar shall exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as may be assigned`
  line `to him by this Act or the Statutes or by the Director.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (23528)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 21
  title `Other authorities and officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23528&sectionno=19&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The powers and duties of authorities and officers other than`
  line `those mentioned above shall be determined by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (23529)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 22
  title `Grants by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23529&sectionno=20&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of enabling the Institutes to discharge their`
  line `functions efficiently under this Act, the Central Government may, after due appropriation made by`
  line `Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to every Institute in each financial year such sums of money and in`
  line `such manner as it may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (23530)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 23
  title `Fund of Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23530&sectionno=21&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Institute shall maintain a Fund to which shall be credited,--`
  line
  line `(a) all moneys provided by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) all fees and other charges received by the Institute;`
  line
  line `(c) all moneys received by the Institute by way of grants, gifts, donations, benefactions, bequests`
  line `or transfers; and`
  line
  line `(d) all moneys received by the Institute in any other manner or from any other source.`
  line
  line `(2) All moneys credited to the Fund of every Institute shall be deposited in such banks or invested in`
  line `such manner as the Institute may, with the approval of the Central Government, decide.`
  line
  line `(3) The Fund of every Institute shall be applied towards meeting the expenses of the Institute`
  line `including expenses incurred in the exercise of its powers and discharge of its duties under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (23531)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 24
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23531&sectionno=22&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Institute shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant`
  line `records and prepare an annual statement of accounts including the balance sheet in such form as may be`
  line `specified by notification, by the Central Government in consultation with the Comptroller and`
  line `Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of every Institute shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor- General of India`
  line `and any expenditure incurred by him in connection with such audit shall be payable by the Institute to the`
  line `Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of the accounts of any Institute shall have the same rights, privileges and authority in`
  line `connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India has in connection with the`
  line `audit of the Government accounts, and, in particular shall have the rights to demand the production of`
  line `books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect the offices of the`
  line Institute.
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of every institute as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or`
  line `any other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament in accordance with such procedure as may be laid down by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (23532)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 25
  title `Pension and provident fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23532&sectionno=23&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Every Institute shall constitute for the benefit of its employees`
  line `such provident or pension fund or provide such insurance scheme as it may deem fit in such manner and`
  line `subject to such conditions as may be prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (23533)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 26
  title Appointments.
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes `1. The words "and Deputy Director" omitted by Act of 28 of 2012, s.12 (w. e. f 7-6-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23533&sectionno=24&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `All appointments of the staff of every Institute, except that of the Director ^1***, shall be made in accordance with the procedure laid down in the Statutes, by--`
  line
  line `(a) the Board, if the appointment is made on the academic staff in the post of Lecturer or above`
  line `or if the appointment is made on the non-academic staff in any cadre the maximum of the pay scale`
  line `for which exceeds rupees ten thousand five hundred;`
  line
  line `(b) the Director, in any other case.`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (23534)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 27
  title Statutes.
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23534&sectionno=25&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Statutes may provide for all or any of the`
  line `following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the conferment of honorary degrees;`
  line
  line `(b) the formation of departments of teaching:`
  line
  line `(c) the fees to be charged for courses of study in the Institute and for admission to the`
  line `examinations of degrees and diplomas of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(d) the institution of fellowships, scholarships, exhibitions, medals and prizes.`
  line
  line `(e) the term of office and the method of appointment of officers of the institute;`
  line
  line `(f) the qualifications of teachers of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(g) the classification, the method of appointment and the determination of the terms and`
  line `conditions of service of teachers and other staff of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(h) the constitution of pension, insurance and provident funds for the benefit of the officers,`
  line `teachers and other staff of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(i) the constitution, powers and duties of the authorities of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(j) the establishment and maintenance of halls and hostels;`
  line
  line `(k) the conditions of residence of students of the Institute and the levying of fees for residence in`
  line `the halls and hostels and of other charges;`
  line
  line `(l) the allowances to be paid to the Chairperson and members of the Board;`
  line
  line `(m) the authentication of the orders and decisions of the Board; and`
  line
  line `(n) the meetings of the Board, the Senate, or any Committee, the quorum at such meetings and the`
  line `procedure to be followed in the conduct of their business.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (23535)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 28
  title `Statutes how made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23535&sectionno=26&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The first Statutes of each Institute shall be framed by the Central`
  line `Government with the prior approval of the Visitor and a copy of the same shall be laid as soon as may be`
  line `before each House of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may, from time to time, make new or additional Statutes or may amend or repeal the`
  line `Statutes in the manner provided in this section.`
  line
  line `(3) Every new Statute or addition to the Statutes or any amendment or repeal of Statutes shall require`
  line `the previous approval of the Visitor who may grant assent or withhold assent or remit it to the Board for`
  line consideration.
  line
  line `(4) A new Statute or a Statute amending or repealing an existing Statute shall have no validity unless`
  line `it has been assented to by the Visitor.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (23536)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 29
  title Ordinances.
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23536&sectionno=27&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act and the Statutes, the Ordinances of every`
  line `Institute may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the admission of the students to the Institute;`
  line
  line `(b) the courses of study to be laid down for all degrees and diplomas of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(c) the conditions under which students shall be admitted to the degree or diploma courses and to`
  line `the examinations of the Institute, and shall be eligible for degrees and diplomas;`
  line
  line `(d) the conditions of award of the fellowships, scholarships, exhibitions, medals and prizes;`
  line
  line `(e) the conditions and mode of appointment and duties of examining bodies, examiners and`
  line moderators;
  line `(f) the conduct of examinations;`
  line
  line `(g) the maintenance of discipline among the students of the Institute; and`
  line
  line `(h) any other matter which by this Act or the Statutes is to be or may be provided for by the`
  line Ordinances.
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (23537)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 30
  title `Ordinances how made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23537&sectionno=28&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this section, Ordinances shall be`
  line `made by the Senate.`
  line
  line `(2) All Ordinances made by the Senate shall have effect from such date as it may direct, but every`
  line `Ordinance so made shall be submitted, as soon as may be, to the Board and shall be considered by the`
  line `Board at its next meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall have power by resolution to modify or cancel any such Ordinance and such`
  line `Ordinance shall from the date of such resolution stand modified accordingly or cancelled, as the case may`
  line be.
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (23538)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 31
  title `Tribunal of Arbitration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23538&sectionno=29&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any dispute arising out of a contract between an Institute and any`
  line `of its employees shall, at the request of the employee concerned or at the instance of the Institute, be`
  line `referred to a Tribunal of Arbitration consisting of one member appointed by the Institute, one member`
  line `nominated by the employee, and an umpire appointed by the Visitor.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Tribunal shall be final and shall not be questioned in any court.`
  line
  line `(3) No suit or proceeding shall lie in any court in respect of any matter, which is required by`
  line `sub-section (1) to be referred to the Tribunal of Arbitration.`
  line
  line `(4) The Tribunal of Arbitration shall have power to regulate its own procedure.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in any law for the time being in force relating to arbitration shall apply to arbitrations`
  line `under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (23539)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 32
  title `Establishment of Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23539&sectionno=30&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, specify in this behalf, there shall be established for all the Institutes specified in column (3)`
  line `of the ^1[First Schedule] ,^2[the Second Schedule and the Third Schedule] a central body to be called the`
  line Council.
  line
  line `(2) The Council shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Minister in charge of the Ministry or Department of the Central Government having`
  line `administrative control of the technical education, ex officio, as Chairman;`
  line
  line `(b) the Secretary to the Government of India in charge of the Ministry or Department of the`
  line `Central Government having administrative control of the technical education, ex officio, as`
  line Vice-Chairman;
  line
  line `(c) the Chairperson of every Board, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) the Director of every Institute, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) the Chairman, University Grants Commission, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(f) the Director General, Council of Scientific and Industrial Research, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(g) four Secretaries to the Government of India, to represent the Ministries or Departments of the`
  line `Central Government dealing with biotechnology, atomic energy, information technology and space,`
  line `ex officio;`
  line
  line `(h) the Chairman, All India Council for Technical Education, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(i) not less than three, but not more than five persons to be nominated by the Visitor, at least one`
  line `of whom shall be a woman, having special knowledge or practical experience in respect of education,`
  line `industry, science or technology;`
  line
  line `(j) three members of Parliament, of whom two shall be chosen by the House of the People and`
  line `one by the Council of States:`
  line
  line `Provided that the office of member of the Council shall not disqualify its holder for being chosen`
  line `as or for being, a member of either House of Parliament;`
  line
  line `(k) two Secretaries to the State Government, from amongst the Ministries or Departments of that`
  line `Government dealing with technical education where the Institutes are located, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(l) Financial Advisor, dealing with the Human Resource Development Ministry or Department of`
  line `the Central Government, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(m) one officer not below the rank of Joint Secretary to the Government of India in the Ministry`
  line `or Department of Central Government having administrative control of the Technical Education, ex`
  line `officio, as Member-Secretary.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act of 28 of 2012, s. 13 for "Schedule" (w. e. f 7-6-2012).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 9 of 2014, s.7 (w.e.f. 4-3-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_30_a:
  sectionId (23540)
  sectionNo 30A
  orderNo 33
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23540&sectionno=30A&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_30_a_content:
  string
  line `[30A. Establishment of Council for the Institutes of Second ScheduleIns.] Ins. by the National`
  line `Institutes of Technology (Amendment) Act, 2012 (28 of 2012), s. 9 (w.e.f. 7-6-2012) and omitted by the`
  line `National Institutes of Technology, Science Education and Research (Amendment) Act, 2014 (9 of 2014), s. 8 (w.e.f. 4-3-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_30_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (23646)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 34
  title `Term of office of, vacancies among, and allowances payable to members of Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23646&sectionno=31&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The terms of office of a member shall be three years from the date of notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that the term of office of an ex officio member shall continue so long as he holds office by`
  line `virtue of which he is such a member.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of a member elected under clause (j) of sub-section (2) of section 30 ^1*** shall`
  line `expire as soon as he ceases to be member of the House, which elected him.`
  line
  line `(3) The term of office of a member nominated or elected to fill a casual vacancy shall continue for the`
  line `remainder of the term of the member in whose place he has been appointed.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section an outgoing member shall, unless the Central`
  line `Government otherwise directs, continue in office until another person is appointed as a member in his`
  line place.
  line
  line `(5) The members of the Council other than ex officio member shall be paid such travelling and other`
  line `allowances as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words, brackets, letters and figures "and clause (j) of sub-section (2) of section 30A" omitted by Act of 9 of 2014, s.9`
  line `(w.e.f. 4-3-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (23647)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 35
  title `Functions of Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23647&sectionno=32&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the general duty of the Council to co-ordinate the activities`
  line `of all the Institutes.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Council shall perform the following`
  line `functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) to advise on matters relating to the duration of the courses, the degrees and other academic`
  line `distinctions to be conferred by the Institutes, admission standards and other academic matters;`
  line
  line `(b) to lay down policy regarding cadres, methods of recruitment and conditions of service of`
  line `employees, institution of scholarships and free ships, levying of fees and other matters of common`
  line interest;
  line
  line `(c) to examine the development plans of each Institute and to approve such of them as are`
  line `considered necessary and also to indicate broadly the financial implications of such approved plans;`
  line
  line `(d) to advise the Visitor, if so required, in respect of any function to be performed by him under`
  line `this Act; and`
  line
  line `(e) to perform such other functions as are assigned to it by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (23648)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 36
  title `Chairman of Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23648&sectionno=33&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairman of the Council shall ordinarily preside at the meetings`
  line `of the Council:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in his absence, the Vice-Chairman of the Council shall preside at the meetings of the`
  line Council.
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of the Chairman of the Council to ensure that the decisions taken by the`
  line `Council are implemented.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairman shall exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as are assigned to`
  line `him by this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The Council shall meet once in every year and follow such procedure in its meetings as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (23649)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 37
  title `Power to make rules in respect of matters in this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23649&sectionno=34&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may,`
  line `by notification, make rules to carry out the purposes of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the travelling and other allowances payable to members of the Council under sub-section (5) of section 31; and`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure to be followed in the meetings of the Council under sub-section (4) of section 33.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Chapter shall be laid, as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of`
  line `the session, immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (23650)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 38
  title `Acts and proceedings not to be invalidated by vacancies, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23650&sectionno=35&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `No act of the Council, or any`
  line `Institute or Board or Senate or any other body set up under this Act or the Statutes, shall be invalid merely`
  line `by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy or defect in the constitution thereof, or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the election, nomination or appointment of a person acting as a member thereof,`
  line or
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in its procedure not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (23651)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23651&sectionno=36&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to it to be necessary or expedient for`
  line `removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the date on`
  line `which this Act receives the assent of the President.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (23652)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 40
  title `Transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079&sectionId=23652&sectionno=37&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00027_200729_1517807327079
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act--`
  line
  line `(a) the Board of Governors of every Institute ^1[mentioned in the First Schedule] functioning as`
  line `such immediately before the commencement of this Act shall continue to so function until a new`
  line `Board is constituted for that Institute under this Act, but on the constitution of a new Board under this`
  line `Act, the member of the Board holding office before such constitution shall cease to hold office;`
  line
  line `(b) every Senate constituted in relation to every Institute before the commencement of this Act`
  line `shall be deemed to be the Senate constituted under this Act until a Senate is constituted under this Act`
  line `for that Institute but on the constitution of new Senate under this Act, the members of the Senate`
  line `holding office before such constitution shall cease to hold office.`
  line
  line `^1[(c) recruitment process and disciplinary proceedings, which had commenced before the`
  line `commencement of the National Institutes of Technology (Amendment) Act, 2012 (28 of 2012), shall`
  line `be completed, mutatis mutandis, in accordance with the relevant provisions in force immediately`
  line `before such commencement.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Recruitment process for a post may be taken to have commenced from the date of`
  line `publication of the advertisement inviting application for the post, and disciplinary proceedings against`
  line `an employee of the Institute may be taken to have commenced on the date of issue of charge sheet for`
  line `major penalty of show cause notice for minor penalty to such employee;`
  line
  line `(d) all matters, which are meant to be provided through Statutes and Ordinances under`
  line `sections 25 and 27, respectively, shall, till such Statutes and Ordinances are made, be governed,`
  line `mutatis mutandis, by the corresponding provisions in force immediately before the commencement of`
  line `this Act.]`
  line
  line `^2[(e) the court, the Academic Council and the Executive Council of the Bengal Engineering and`
  line `Science University, Shibpur performing functions as such immediately before the commencement of`
  line `the National Institutes of Technology, Science Education and Research (Amendment Act, 2014`
  line `(9 of 2914), shall continue to function until a Board is constituted for the Indian Institute of`
  line `Engineering Science and Technology, Shibpur under this Act, but on and after the constitution of a`
  line `Board under this Act, the members of the Court, the Academic Council and the Executive Council,`
  line `shall cease to hold office;`
  line
  line `(f) the authorities of the Bengal Engineering and Science University, Shibpur, by whatever names`
  line `so called, performing functions as such immediately before the commencement of the National`
  line `Institutes of Technology, Science Education and Research (Amendment) Act, 2014 (9 of 2014) shall`
  line `continue to function until a new Authority is appointed or constituted for performing the same`
  line `functions under the said Act, but on and after such appointment or constitution, the authorities`
  line `performing the functions under the Bengal Engineering and Science University, Shibpur Act, 2014`
  line `(13 of 2004) or any Statutes or Ordinances made thereunder shall cease to hold office;`
  line
  line `(g) every Senate or any other authorities in the names so called constituted in relation to every`
  line `Institute before the commencement of the National Institutes of Technology, Science Education and`
  line `Research (Amendment) Act, 2014 shall be deemed to be the Senate constituted under the said Act`
  line `until a new Senate is constituted under this Act for that Institute, but on the constitution of a new`
  line `Senate under this Act, the members of the Senate holding office before such constitution shall cease`
  line `to hold office;`
  line
  line `(h) until the first Statutes and the Ordinances are made and brought in force under the National`
  line `Institutes of Technology, Science Education and Research (Amendment) Act, 2014 (9 of 2014) the`
  line `Statutes, Ordinances and rules made for the Bengal Engineering and Science University, Shibpur`
  line `immediately before the commencement of the said Act shall continue to apply to the Indian Institute`
  line `of Engineering Science and Technology, Shibpur in so far as they are not inconsistent with the`
  line `provisions of the said Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2012, s.16 (w.e.f. 7-6-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 9 of 2014, s.10 (w.e.f. 4-3-2014).`
